# bernardoprd — portfolio

Personal portfolio website for Bernardo Prudêncio, Senior Product Designer based in Barcelona.

## Stack

Pure HTML/CSS/JS — no build step, no framework, no dependencies except Google Fonts. Deployable anywhere.

## Files

```
index.html          → Main portfolio (hero, about, selected work, experience, education, contact)
star-sitter.html    → Star Sitter program case study
README.md           → This file
```

## Local development

Just open `index.html` in a browser. No server needed.

```bash
open index.html
```

## Deployment

Hosted via **GitHub Pages** or **Vercel**. Any push to `main` triggers a deploy.

### GitHub Pages setup
1. Repo Settings → Pages
2. Source: `main` branch, `/ (root)`
3. Save — live at `https://USERNAME.github.io/REPO`

### Custom domain
Add a `CNAME` file with your domain (e.g. `bernardoprd.com`), then point your DNS to GitHub's servers.

## Adding new case studies

Each case study is a standalone HTML file. Copy `star-sitter.html` as a template — it shares the same CSS variables, fonts, header, and cursor as `index.html`.

Update the project card link in `index.html`:
```html
<a class="project-item" href="your-case-study.html">
```

## Design system

| Token | Value | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `--bg` | `#0c0c0b` | Page background |
| `--text` | `#f0ede6` | Primary text |
| `--mid` | `#888880` | Secondary text |
| `--muted` | `#4a4a46` | Tertiary / dates |
| `--rule` | `rgba(240,237,230,0.12)` | Dividers |
| Font | Syne + Syne Mono | Google Fonts |

## Content source

Portfolio content is maintained in Notion at `bernardoprd.notion.site` and synced manually into HTML.
